Sentencas: The ultra-high vacuum surface preparation of heteroepitaxial lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite thin films has been studied using soft X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy.
Titulo: Surface evolution of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite thin films at low temperatures

Sentencas: Specifically, the effect of annealing the films at low temperatures in low partial pressures of oxygen and argon has been investigated.
Titulo: Surface evolution of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite thin films at low temperatures

Sentencas: We find that atmospheric surface carbon contamination of the films can be removed in select anneal temperature regimes in argon, but remains bound to the surface with oxygen annealing at any temperature.
Titulo: Surface evolution of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite thin films at low temperatures

Sentencas: Irrespective of the gas used, an insulating phase transition occurs near 300 degrees C due to strontium segregation at the surface.
Titulo: Surface evolution of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite thin films at low temperatures

Sentencas: The surface develops more insulating character if annealed with oxygen.
Titulo: Surface evolution of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite thin films at low temperatures

Sentencas: Different species are proposed to be responsible for the discrepancy in insulating character.
Titulo: Surface evolution of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite thin films at low temperatures
